event: message_saved
data: {"messageId":"ZqNeu3Gs2n27CUcbyDRL6","role":"user","content":"Perform a comprehensive observability audit of the entire OpenAgentic platform. This is the final validation test - use EVERY monitoring tool available:\n\n1. PROMETHEUS MONITORING:\n   - Use prometheus_health_summary for overall monitoring health\n   - Use prometheus_targets to list all scrape targets and their status\n   - Use prometheus_alerts to check for any active alerts\n   - Use prometheus_query with query 'up' to check all service availability\n   - Use prometheus_query_range with query 'rate(http_requests_total[5m])' for the last hour to show request rate\n   - Use prometheus_metrics_list to show available metrics\n\n2. LOKI LOG ANALYSIS:\n   - Use loki_labels to show all available log labels\n   - Use loki_label_values for label 'container' to show all logging containers\n   - Use loki_search_errors for namespace 'agentic-dev' in the last 2 hours\n   - Use loki_count_logs for the query '{namespace=\"agentic-dev\"}' to show log volume\n   - Use loki_log_rate for '{namespace=\"agentic-dev\"}' to show log rate trends\n\n3. KUBERNETES STATE:\n   - Use k8s_cluster_health for overall cluster status\n   - Use k8s_list_nodes to show node health and resource usage\n   - Use k8s_get_events in namespace agentic-dev for the last hour\n   - Use k8s_list_pods in agentic-dev to check all pod statuses\n\n4. APPLICATION STATE:\n   - Use admin_full_system_test for end-to-end application test\n   - Use admin_system_infrastructure_health_check for infrastructure summary\n   - Use flowise_health_check for workflow engine status\n\n5. SYNTHESIS REPORT:\n   Create a comprehensive 'Platform Health Dashboard' showing:\n   - Overall platform health score (0-100)\n   - Per-service health status\n   - Active alerts and warnings\n   - Resource utilization trends\n   - Log error rate trends\n   - Recommendations for improvement\n\nExecute ALL tool calls. This is the comprehensive final check.","timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:11:33.887Z","source":"database","confirmed":true}

