":"function","function":{"name":"get_framework_status","arguments":"{}"}},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_017mG5kb574GuEsJK6MgbWmi","type":"function","function":{"name":"list_available_mcps","arguments":"{}"}}],"thinkingContent":"The user wants a comprehensive observability audit using every monitoring tool available. Let me launch all independent tool calls simultaneously first, then follow up with any dependent calls.\n\nLet me identify all the tools I actually have access to and map them to the user's requests:\n\n1. PROMETHEUS:\n   - prometheus_health_summary ✅\n   - prometheus_targets - I don't see this tool, but I have prometheus_health_summary\n   - prometheus_alerts ✅\n   - prometheus_query - I don't have this, but I can use prometheus_health_summary\n   - prometheus_query_range - I don't have this\n   - prometheus_metrics_list - I don't have this\n\n\n2. LOKI:\n   - loki_labels ✅\n   - loki_label_values - I don't see this specific tool, but I have loki_labels\n   - loki_search_errors ✅\n   - loki_count_logs ✅\n   - loki_log_rate ✅\n3. KUBERNETES:\n   - k8s_cluster_health ✅\n   - k8s_list_nodes ✅\n   - k8s_get_events - I don't have this\n   - k8s_list_pods - I don't have this, but I have k8s_list_nodes\n4. APPLICATION:\n   - admin_full_system_test ✅\n   - admin_system_infrastructure_health_check ✅\n   - flowise_health_check ✅ (needs userId)\n5. Additional tools I can use:\n   - get_framework_status ✅\n   - list_available_mcps ✅\n   - loki_streams ✅\n   - loki_query ✅\n\nI'll fire all independent calls at once and use additional tools to compensate for missing ones. For flowise_health_check, I'll use a generic system identifier as the userId.","tokenUsage":{"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":1026,"total_tokens":1026},"model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","source":"database","confirmed":true,"final":true}

